text editors:
gedit = gui
nano = cli
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
touch - creates a txt file
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
stop a process - control c
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ls -l
rwxrwxrwx {hardlinkNo} {Owner} {Owner} {byte size} {ModdedMonth} {ModdedDay} {ModdedTime} {fileName}

white - file
dark blue - folder
light blue - link
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ps aux
lists {user} {PID} {CPU%} {MEM%} {blah} {blah} {command}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ln {File}
makes a hardlink to a file. Synched dupe but doesn't corrupt if the original is deleted
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ln -s {File}
makes a softlink to a file. Synched dupe but does corrupt if the original is deleted
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sudo apt install - install a new package or a newer version of an already installed package on the system
sudo apt upgrade - upgrades the installed packages to the latest available versions
sudo apt update - updates the package lists
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
bash
runs a file as a set of terminal commands
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
head/tail -{n} {file}
shows the first/last n lines of a file
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
echo "{data}"
prints data into the cli
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
>
redirect output, open as write
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>
redirect output, Open as append
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
|
Pipe operator for joining commands (i.e cat | grep)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
sudo fdisk -l
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
grep {data} {file}
looks for and highlights words / only gets rows with {data}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
at now + {n} minutes â€“f {script}
run a line of a script every n minutes
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
whoami
Displays current user
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sudo useradd
Adds a user with no config
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sudo adduser
Adds a user with full config
